<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-02-04T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-02-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">875.6363/157: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-04T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 4,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>6. The Standard Oil Company of New York informs the Department that it
                            has received word of renewed activity on the part of Anglo-Persian in
                            Albania. The company is disposed to send a representative to Albania
                            should the situation warrant. Please make a brief telegraphic
                            report.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>